-py3-none-any.whl\", hash = \"sha256:1380560bdba02b6b6c90de54133c81c9f2a453dee9912fe58c1dcced1edb7cff\", size = 46814, upload-time = \"2025-10-06T14:12:53.872Z\" },\n ]\n \n [[package]]\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "FedRAMP Vulnerability Remediation - 2025-12-04\n# FedRAMP Vulnerability Remediation - 2025-12-04\n\n**Due Date**: 2025-12-18\n**Tracking Issue**: [h2oai/cloud-platform#897](https://github.com/h2oai/cloud-platform/issues/897)\n\n## \u26a0\ufe0f Important Information\n\n### Remediation Timeline\n\nPer [FedRAMP vulnerability scanning requirements](https://www.fedramp.gov/assets/resources/documents/CSP_Vulnerability_Scanning_Requirements.pdf) and [NIST SP 800-53 RA-5](https://csrc.nist.gov/projects/cprt/catalog#/cprt/framework/version/SP_800_53_5_1_1/home?element=RA-5):\n\n| Severity | Remediation Timeline |\n|----------|----------------------|\n| **CRITICAL** | 30 days |\n| **HIGH** | 30 days |\n| **MEDIUM** | 90 days |\n| **LOW** | 180 days |\n\n### Version Notice\n\n\u26a0\ufe0f **The image versions listed below may not represent the most recent versions available.** Please verify that the vulnerabilities still exist in the latest version of each image before beginning remediation work.\n\n### Verifying Vulnerabilities with Trivy\n\nThese scan results were generated using [Trivy](https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy). To verify vulnerabilities locally:\n\n```bash\n# Scan a specific image\ntrivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL <image-name>:<tag>\n\n# Scan with detailed output\ntrivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --format table <image-name>:<tag>\n\n# Generate JSON output for processing\ntrivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --format json -o results.json <image-name>:<tag>\n```\n\n---\n\n## Vulnerabilities by Image\n\n## h2oai-llmstudio-app-stg:v1.14.2\n\n| CVE | Severity | Packages | Version | Fix | Description |\n|-----|----------|----------|---------|-----|-------------|\n| CVE-2024-27407 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  fs/ntfs3: Fixed overflow check ... |\n| CVE-2024-35870 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  smb: client: fix UAF in smb2_re... |\n| CVE-2024-53179 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  smb: client: fix use-after-free... |\n| CVE-2025-38118 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  Bluetooth: MGMT: Fix UAF on mgm... |\n| CVE-2025-38352 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  posix-cpu-timers: fix race betw... |\n| CVE-2025-40300 | high | linux-libc-dev | 5.15.0-151.161 | N/A | In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:  x86/vmscape: Add conditional IB... |\n| CVE-2025-47907 | high | stdlib, stdlib | v1.23.10 | N/A | Cancelling a query (e.g. by cancelling the context passed to one of the query methods) during a call... |\n| CVE-2025-58183 | high | stdlib, stdlib | v1.23.10 | N/A | tar.Reader does not set a maximum size on the number of sparse region data blocks in GNU tar pax 1.0... |\n| CVE-2025-58186 | high | stdlib, stdlib | v1.23.10 | N/A | Despite HTTP headers having a default limit of 1MB, the number of cookies that can be parsed does no... |\n| CVE-2025-58187 | high | stdlib, stdlib | v1.23.10 | N/A | Due to the design of the name constraint checking algorithm, the processing time of some inputs scal... |\n| CVE-2025-58188 | high | stdlib, stdlib | v1.23.10 | N/A | Validating certificate chains which contain DSA public keys can cause programs to panic, due to a in... |\n| CVE-2025-62727 | high | starlette | 0.47.2 | N/A | Starlette is a lightweight ASGI framework/toolkit. Starting in version 0.39.0 and prior to version 0... |\n\n## h2oai-llmstudio-app-stg:v1.14.4